verbs.description: joggle (third-person singular simple present joggles, present participle joggling, simple past and past participle joggled)

entries.meaning: (transitive) To shake slightly; to push suddenly but slightly, so as to cause to shake or totter; to jostle; to jog.
(intransitive) To shake or totter; to slip out of place.
(engineering) A step formed in material by two adjacent reverse bends.
(architecture) A notch or tooth in the joining surface of any piece of building material to prevent slipping.

verbs.description: joggle (third-person singular simple present joggles, present participle joggling, simple past and past participle joggled)

entries.meaning: (architecture, transitive) To join by means of joggles, so as to prevent sliding apart; sometimes, loosely, to dowel.

verbs.description: joggle (third-person singular simple present joggles, present participle joggling, simple past and past participle joggled)

entries.meaning: To jog or run while juggling.
